	<section>
		<h2 id="tools">Tools</h2>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Keyboard-only</strong> — No mouse. Tab, Shift+Tab, Enter, Space, arrows, Escape. Confirm all actions possible and no focus traps (except intentional in modal/search/settings).</li>
			<li><strong>Screen reader</strong> — NVDA (Windows), VoiceOver (macOS: Cmd+F5), or JAWS. Check announcements (labels, state changes, live regions).</li>
			<li><strong>200% zoom</strong> — Test at 200% browser zoom (or 200% text scaling). Content should reflow without horizontal scrolling.</li>
			<li><strong>Increased font size</strong> — Use the Settings font-size slider or OS font-size settings.</li>
			<li><strong>Color blindness / vision</strong> — Browser DevTools (e.g. Chrome Rendering → Emulate vision deficiencies) to check information is not conveyed by color alone.</li>
			<li><strong>axe DevTools</strong> — Browser extension for one-off page scans.</li>
			<li><strong>Lighthouse</strong> — Chrome DevTools → Lighthouse → Accessibility for periodic checks.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2 id="step-by-step-example">Step-by-step example: Modal</h2>
		<p>Use this pattern for other Priority 1 components. Open <a href="/docs/components/modal">Modal</a> and follow in order.</p>
		<ol>
			<li>Tab to the trigger button (“Open modal”). Activate with Enter or Space.</li>
			<li>Confirm focus moves into the dialog (first focusable element or the dialog container).</li>
			<li>Tab and Shift+Tab repeatedly — focus must stay inside the modal (no focus on page behind).</li>
			<li>Press Escape — modal closes and focus returns to the trigger button.</li>
			<li>Re-open the modal. With a screen reader, confirm the dialog is announced (e.g. “dialog” and title/aria-labelledby). Navigate and confirm focus and labels are announced correctly.</li>
		</ol>
	</section>

