	<section>
		<h2 id="screen-reader-keys">Screen reader quick reference</h2>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>NVDA (Windows)</strong> — Tab / Shift+Tab: focus; Down/Up: read next/previous line; Insert+Down: read all; Insert+F7: elements list (headings, landmarks, links).</li>
			<li><strong>VoiceOver (macOS)</strong> — VO+Right/Left: move; VO+Shift+Down: enter group; VO+Shift+Up: leave group; VO+A: read all; VO+U: rotor (headings, links, landmarks).</li>
			<li><strong>JAWS (Windows)</strong> — Tab / Shift+Tab: focus; Down/Up: read; Insert+Down: read next; Insert+F7: links list; Insert+F6: headings list.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2 id="suggested-order">Suggested order</h2>
		<ol>
			<li>Keyboard-only pass on Priority 1 (Modal, Dropdown, Theme Switcher, Font Switcher, Settings, Tabs, Search, Accordion). Fix focus and traps.</li>
			<li>Screen reader pass on the same. Fix labels and announcements.</li>
			<li>axe DevTools on those pages. Fix reported issues.</li>
			<li>Repeat for Priority 2 and 3; update <a href="/docs/accessibility#best-practices">Best practices</a> if you find new patterns.</li>
		</ol>
	</section>
